This paper deals with the topics of content distribution, fingerprinting, and traitor tracing, which are all relevant to the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on multimedia content distribution, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). The use of segment-wise construction of fingerprints and the traitor-tracing algorithm also suggest a possible connection to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method, which could be relevant to the sub-category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
